Day of victory in Islamic revolution in Iran observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 11 (KCNA) -- Minju Joson today devotes an article to the 22nd anniversary of the victory in the Islamic revolution in Iran.
 Following the victory in the revolution, the Iranian people have stood against the imperialists' incessant moves for aggression and interference and intensified the struggle to build new independent and prosperous Iran, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are decisively countering any anti-Iranian and anti-Islamic attempt, holding high the banner of independence against imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are strongly opposed to U.S. forces' presence in the Persian Gulf region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Externally, the Iranian government has developed friendly and cooperative relations with the countries of the Persian Gulf region and other countries of the world on the principle of equality and non-interference in other's internal affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The peoples of the DPRK and Iran have the common anti-imperialist independent stand and the bonds of friendship between the two governments and peoples are therefore, growing stronger as the days go by. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people sincerely wish the Iranian people greater success in their future work for independence and national prosperity.

Annual meeting of Malagasy national committee for study of Juche idea held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 11 (KCNA) -- The Malagasy national committee for the study of the Juche idea held an annual meeting on January 31.
 A report of the chairman of the committee was followed by speeches at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting discussed the issues of deepening the study of the famous works of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il to grasp the greatness and the truth of the Juche idea, steadily expanding the ranks of Juche idea study organizations and intensifying the dissemination of the idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also discussed matters of celebrating the birthday of Kim Jong Il and Sun's Day this year and next year as grand festivals common to humankind and waging positive activities to support the Korean people in their struggle to reunify the country.

Imperialists' talk about peace under fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 11 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article says that the imperialists' sham "peace" offensive based on their world strategy constitutes a major factor of threatening the world people's cause of independence, progress and peace.
 The imperialists are working hard to dominate other countries and nations, weaken and contain the independent forces of the world, while paying lip-service to "peace," the article says, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world revolutionary people should clearly see through the danger lurking  behind imperialists' noisy clamour about disarmament. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an unchangeable strategy of the U.S. conservative hardliners to dominate the world with strength in the 21st century, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. moves to establish its "National Missile Defense" system are aimed to monopolize nuclear weapons and missiles in a bid to contain other powers standing for the multi-polarization of the world and realize their strategy of world supremacy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This means a declaration of an arms race and a missile race in the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is set to allot a huge amount of fund for the establishment of the "Theatre Missile Defense" system as requested by the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world revolutionary people should be highly alert against the imperialists getting involved in disputes in various regions and countries and acting a "mediator" and guarantor in settling them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While talking about "peaceful settlement" of disputes, the imperialists are, in fact, adding fuel to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What they really seek is not to find any solution to the disputes but to keep their source and exploit it for their political and military intervention in those countries in dispute. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to guard against Japan, in particular, in its desperate efforts to intervene in world disputes under the cloak of "peacekeeping." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that small nations, anti-imperialist independent countries, have become major targets of the imperialists' sham "peace" offensive, the article observes that the U.S. is busy preparing for a war of aggression in South Korea, though it is loudmouthed about "peace" and "detente" on the Korean peninsula.
